    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Remove 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[25g]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [30g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> from the fridge and set aside to soften slightly</p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> into fries</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mayo-lean-beef-burger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sweet potato fries</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until cooked through and golden \u2013 these are your <strong>smoky sweet potato fries</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mayo-lean-beef-burger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>truffle oil</strong>, <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>truffle & black pepper mayo</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong>, then add to a separate bowl with your <strong>dried oregano</strong> and <strong>softened butter</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic & herb butter</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mayo-lean-beef-burger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Season your<strong> lean beef mince</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Massage the meat with clean hands for 1 min (this helps them to hold their shape whilst cooking)</p><p>Divide the mince and shape them into 1 <strong>patty</strong> per person</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mayo-lean-beef-burger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the fries have been in for 15-20 min, heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>lean beef patty[ies]</strong>, press down firmly with a spatula and cook for 5 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? You may need to do this in batches!</p><p>Flip the <strong>patty[ies]</strong> and reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 3 min further</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mayo-lean-beef-burger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the patty[ies] are cooking, cut your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half and spread them with the<strong> garlic & herb butter</strong></p><p>Add to a baking tray (or two!), butter-side up, and put the tray[s] in the oven for 3-4 min or until golden \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic & herb brioche bun[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mayo-lean-beef-burger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, top the lean beef patty[ies] with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Cover loosely with a lid (or some tin foil!) and cook for 2-3 min further or until the cheese has melted and the patty[ies] are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Meanwhile, wash your<strong> lettuce </strong>and set the <strong>leaves</strong> aside for serving</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mayo-lean-beef-burger-with-sweet-potato-fries/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Spread the base of the<strong> garlic & herb brioche bun</strong> with some <strong>truffle & black pepper mayo</strong></p><p>Build your burger by topping the<strong> base </strong>with some <strong>lettuce leaves</strong>,<strong> </strong>a<strong> cheesy patty </strong>and<strong> </strong>some more <strong>truffle & black pepper mayo</strong> then top with the<strong> lid</strong></p><p>Serve with the <strong>smoky sweet potato fries</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
